Form submit

Mock Interview:

Q1. What is HTML, and why is it used in web development?

Q2. Explain the purpose of basic HTML tags like <html>, <head>, <title>, <body>, and <p>.

Q3. What are the key differences between HTML and HTML5? Mention some new features introduced in HTML5.

Q4. Differentiate between <div>, <section>, and <article> tags in HTML. When would you use each of these tags?

Q5. Compare <div> and <span> tags in HTML. How do they differ in terms of their default display behavior?

Q6. Explain the concept of inline and block-level elements in HTML. Provide examples of each type.

Q7. Describe the structure of HTML forms. What is the purpose of the <form> tag in HTML?

Q8. List common input elements used in HTML forms. Explain their usage and attributes.

Q9. How do you create a submit button in an HTML form using the <input> tag?

Q10. Discuss the different types of form input fields, such as text input, password input, radio buttons, checkboxes, and select dropdowns.

Q11. Explain the action and method attributes of the <form> tag in HTML. What are their roles in form submission?

Q12. What is the purpose of the name attribute in HTML form elements? How is it used when submitting a form?
